FT  17 FEB 94 / Flying bishops
Downing Street yesterday named The Venerable John Gaisford, archdeacon of
Macclesfield, and The Venerable John Richards, archdeacon of Exeter, to
minister to Anglican dioceses opposed to the ordination of women. Archdeacon
Gaisford, 59, will be consecrated Bishop of Beverley, and cover northern
England, and Archdeacon Richards, 60, will become Bishop of Ebbsfleet and
cover southern England.
